WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:03.090
You think you're smarter
than your Mama

00:03.133 --> 00:04.743
because you have an M.D.?
Believe me, you're not.

00:04.787 --> 00:06.789
[ Siren wailing ] Man: Clear center stage.

00:06.832 --> 00:10.445
Woman: Okay, we're on our way in. Clear.

00:10.488 --> 00:11.794
Willis: Free fluid in the ultrasound.

00:11.837 --> 00:15.450
Hold still in there.
Scalpel.

00:15.493 --> 00:17.887
-It's my patient. I'll do it.
-Okay, heart rate dropping.

00:17.930 --> 00:20.498
-Not today.
-Get ready to defibrillate.

00:20.542 --> 00:22.022
Sats are stabilizing.

00:22.065 --> 00:23.806
It's okay. We're gonna take care of you.

00:23.849 --> 00:26.678
I'm not going anywhere.

00:26.722 --> 00:30.247
♪♪

00:30.291 --> 00:33.859
I like it.

00:33.903 --> 00:36.949
I mean, for what it is.

00:39.256 --> 00:41.780
Give us a minute, son.

00:41.824 --> 00:44.957
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

00:45.001 --> 00:47.177
My little girl is
out there somewhere,

00:47.221 --> 00:48.831
and all you can do is
tell me to wait?

00:48.874 --> 00:50.702
We are looking, Dr. Rorish,

00:50.746 --> 00:52.095
but we find that runaways
at her age

00:52.139 --> 00:53.923
are usually with friends.

00:53.966 --> 00:56.099
I told you, we already
checked everyone.All her friends?

00:56.143 --> 00:58.797
Girls don't always tell
their moms about boyfriends.

00:58.841 --> 01:00.190
Her boyfriend just died.

01:00.234 --> 01:02.453
Right. [ Sighs ] Max.

01:02.497 --> 01:04.542
But there are no texts
on her phone with him.

01:04.586 --> 01:07.545
I told you.
She deleted them all.

01:07.589 --> 01:09.069
Her heart was broken.

01:09.112 --> 01:11.984
I understand.
It must've been hard on her.

01:12.028 --> 01:13.508
We'll let you know
when we have more.

01:13.551 --> 01:15.597
Wait, wait, wait. Wait.
What -- I --

01:15.640 --> 01:17.555
I'm just supposed to pace around
my house until then?

01:17.599 --> 01:20.254
She means, "Thank you."

01:21.385 --> 01:23.126
[ Door opens ]

01:23.170 --> 01:25.781
I knew she was lost
when Max died.[ Door closes ]

01:25.824 --> 01:29.176
I should've handled it
differently. [ Sniffles ]

01:29.219 --> 01:32.875
Oh. If anything happens
to her...

01:32.918 --> 01:34.746
♪♪

01:34.790 --> 01:37.097
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

01:37.140 --> 01:40.100
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:40.143 --> 01:41.884
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

01:41.927 --> 01:44.800
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

01:44.843 --> 01:47.150
[ Engine revs ]

01:47.194 --> 01:50.414
-Rox! Okay, okay.
-[ Whimpering ]

01:50.458 --> 01:52.764
It was a hit and run.
You're not my wife.

01:52.808 --> 01:54.679
You're not my girlfriend.
You're not my shrink.

01:54.723 --> 01:56.507
Ethan, she's gonna wake up,
right?

01:56.551 --> 01:59.075
-I need her to live. Hold on.
-Rox!

02:01.904 --> 02:03.775
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

02:03.819 --> 02:07.605
Woman over PA: General Adams,
7635. General Adams, 7635.

02:07.649 --> 02:10.391
Excuse me? Do you have
the results of the scan?

02:10.434 --> 02:12.784
The MRI? We did it over
three hours ago.

02:12.828 --> 02:15.570
-I-I don't know.
-But you know who to ask, right?

02:15.613 --> 02:17.789
The General who performed
the operation?

02:17.833 --> 02:20.183
Please.
Please just go ask him.Okay.

02:20.227 --> 02:23.055
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

02:23.099 --> 02:26.668
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

02:26.711 --> 02:28.278
Dad, you're killing me. Just
tell me what the board said.

02:28.322 --> 02:30.150
We'll talk about it later.

02:30.193 --> 02:31.542
Okay, fine, but you
could at least tell me

02:31.586 --> 02:34.284
what you thought about it.
-I love it...

02:34.328 --> 02:36.591
if I want lawsuits
against my hospital

02:36.634 --> 02:38.375
and my son to waste
his education.

02:38.419 --> 02:41.378
I love it like something
I wish never happened.

02:41.422 --> 02:43.946
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

02:43.989 --> 02:46.340
"The Shining" got panned, too.
What do critics know?

02:46.383 --> 02:48.777
He's never been
short of confidence.

02:48.820 --> 02:52.128
I recognize some of these faces
from the film.

02:52.172 --> 02:53.956
Shouldn't you properly
introduce me?

02:53.999 --> 02:56.524
Everybody, this is my father,
Oscar Avila.

02:56.567 --> 03:01.006
Dr. Savetti, third year,
Dr. Dixon, and Dr. Kean.

03:01.050 --> 03:03.661
-She's the one I told you about.
-Told me what?

03:03.705 --> 03:06.011
You know, you made that
call for her.Uh, what call?

03:06.055 --> 03:07.796
-No idea.
-Doesn't matter.

03:07.839 --> 03:10.102
Oh, wait.
Is this the OB thing?

03:10.146 --> 03:13.018
Yeah. My assistant did that,
but you'll get it.

03:13.062 --> 03:15.456
Okay, people, let's gather.

03:15.499 --> 03:17.153
Leanne hasn't gotten any news
on Ariel,

03:17.197 --> 03:18.937
and Willis is still with Rox.

03:18.981 --> 03:20.678
We're down
two excellent doctors,

03:20.722 --> 03:23.203
which means...we're gonna
have to step it up.

03:23.246 --> 03:24.682
Let's make 'em proud.

03:24.726 --> 03:26.510
Should be easy.
It's super slow today.

03:26.554 --> 03:28.033
[ Groans ]You never say that.
What are you doing?

03:28.077 --> 03:29.905
[ Door opens ]We've got incoming.

03:29.948 --> 03:32.342
Jesse:
Okay, guys. Let's go. Come on.

03:32.386 --> 03:37.260
[ Sirens wailing ]

03:37.304 --> 03:39.915
Hey, can we get some help
over here?What happened?

03:39.958 --> 03:41.786
Campus Spring Fling,
and the stage just blew over.

03:41.830 --> 03:43.353
Not enough ambulances,
so some of us

03:43.397 --> 03:45.399
just started grabbing people
and bringing 'em in.

03:45.442 --> 03:48.880
This is Logan.Crowd was going crazy.
[ Coughs ] I got trampled.

03:48.924 --> 03:51.143
-Are you in any pain?
-In my chest.

03:51.187 --> 03:52.797
How many people were hurt
back there?

03:52.841 --> 03:55.060
-No idea.
-What do you got?

03:55.104 --> 03:57.411
19-year-old male with
crush injury to the abdomen.

03:57.454 --> 04:00.065
-Pulseless on arrival.
-How long's he been down?

04:00.109 --> 04:02.764
Compressions for 10 minutes.
Never regained pulses.

04:02.807 --> 04:04.635
Let's go.
What have you got?

04:04.679 --> 04:06.681
40-year-old female,
32 weeks pregnant.

04:06.724 --> 04:08.248
Pillar fell on right leg.
Obvious deformity.

04:08.291 --> 04:09.988
-No distal pulses.
-Can you tell me your name?

04:10.032 --> 04:12.382
Keri. Is my baby okay?

04:12.426 --> 04:15.255
We're gonna find out.
Let's go.

04:15.298 --> 04:19.998
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:20.042 --> 04:21.522
Mario: Somebody call an OB.

04:21.565 --> 04:23.175
We need
a portable fetal monitor.

04:23.219 --> 04:26.614
-On my count. Ready? One, two...
-I can't deliver yet.

04:26.657 --> 04:28.703
She needs at least
four more weeks.

04:28.746 --> 04:31.749
-Intubation kit.
-B-lines. Pleural effusion.

04:31.793 --> 04:35.100
Get a chest x-ray now.

04:35.144 --> 04:38.321
-I paged everybody to come in.
-Thanks, Risa.

04:38.365 --> 04:39.931
Not Leanne, right?

04:39.975 --> 04:43.544
She's on the list.
She was paged automatically.

04:43.587 --> 04:46.111
-Pulse check.
-Nothing.

04:46.155 --> 04:48.679
-20 minutes down.
-Cardiac standstill.

04:48.723 --> 04:50.420
Any suggestions?

04:50.464 --> 04:53.205
[ Monitor emitting
continuous tone ]

04:53.249 --> 04:56.992
Time of death -- 11:07 A.M.[ Click, beep ]

04:57.035 --> 04:58.907
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:58.950 --> 05:00.909
Where do you want this one?We don't have room
for that bed.

05:00.952 --> 05:02.345
We have too many people
out there. What do you
want me to do?

05:02.389 --> 05:04.391
-Hey.
-This patient's...

05:04.434 --> 05:06.306
Can we get more doctors
out there?Which bed are we swapping out?

05:06.349 --> 05:09.134
-Everybody, stay focused!
-There's too many out there.

05:09.178 --> 05:11.615
[ Speaking over each other ]

05:11.659 --> 05:14.226
Hey, hey, hey!
Risa, move that bed out.

05:14.270 --> 05:15.750
Elliot on the next one.
Noa with Diego.

05:15.793 --> 05:17.273
Jesse, give me a hand over here.

05:17.317 --> 05:19.928
Last I heard, you weren't
an attending yet.

05:19.971 --> 05:21.973
I'm senior to you. Move.

05:22.017 --> 05:24.324
Okay. It's okay.

05:24.367 --> 05:27.631
♪♪

05:27.675 --> 05:29.633
She's been here a week.
It's time to wake her up.

05:29.677 --> 05:31.331
Have you slept at all
since you've been here?

05:31.374 --> 05:32.984
Her CK levels are
through the roof.
She's got pneumonia.

05:33.028 --> 05:34.464
I'm not taking her
out of the coma

05:34.508 --> 05:36.597
until her swelling decreases
to my satisfaction.

05:36.640 --> 05:39.382
Her kidneys are failing.That's reversible.
Death is not.

05:39.426 --> 05:40.775
You're gonna kill her
playing it safe.

05:40.818 --> 05:42.211
Watch your tone, Colonel.

05:42.254 --> 05:44.213
I'm your superior officer,
and not a patient one.

05:44.256 --> 05:45.562
Now you're not allowed
back in that room

05:45.606 --> 05:49.610
until you've rested.
And put on a damn uniform.

05:49.653 --> 05:52.482
♪♪

05:52.526 --> 05:54.484
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over PA ]

05:54.528 --> 05:56.443
What are you looking at?

05:56.486 --> 05:58.836
-Will you take a look at this?
-I don't work here.

05:58.880 --> 06:00.403
But you're a doctor, right?

06:00.447 --> 06:02.666
Don't I look like a guy
who needs a doctor?

06:02.710 --> 06:08.193
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

06:08.237 --> 06:10.500
Whoa. Oh, hang on.

06:10.544 --> 06:12.502
♪♪

06:12.546 --> 06:14.025
No.

06:14.069 --> 06:15.070
♪♪

06:23.470 --> 06:24.906
This can't be happening.
This can't be happening.

06:24.949 --> 06:26.908
No perfusion. Keri,
we need to reset your leg.

06:26.951 --> 06:28.344
No, my baby is more important.
Please.

06:28.388 --> 06:29.867
And we're gonna save both.

06:29.911 --> 06:31.347
But first, we have to get
blood flow back to your leg.

06:31.391 --> 06:32.522
One, two...

06:32.566 --> 06:35.046
[ Screams loudly ]

06:35.090 --> 06:37.135
[ Sobbing ]

06:37.179 --> 06:39.529
Pressure's dropping.
Diego, I need that
scalp bleeder stopped now.

06:39.573 --> 06:42.053
-Tie faster.
-[ Crying ]

06:42.097 --> 06:44.055
Tie faster.

06:44.099 --> 06:47.189
You know what? Staples are
much faster. Watch.

06:47.232 --> 06:49.539
Diego, focus. Staples aren't
enough to stop the bleed here.

06:49.583 --> 06:52.716
Dr. Kean, suture the wound.

06:52.760 --> 06:54.675
[ Whimpers ]

06:54.718 --> 06:56.590
Good cardiac activity.
No placental abruption.What does that mean?

06:56.633 --> 06:57.982
It means your baby's
doing great.

06:58.026 --> 07:00.550
OB's on their way down
to make sure, okay?

07:00.594 --> 07:02.987
Dr. Campbell.Dr. Savetti,
looks like you got this.

07:03.031 --> 07:05.468
-[ Panting ]
-Jesse: Okay.

07:05.512 --> 07:06.904
Dr. Rorish.

07:06.948 --> 07:08.602
I-I was paged.

07:08.645 --> 07:10.865
Leanne.No, no, no, no.
I need to be helpful.

07:10.908 --> 07:13.868
Uh, I'll get a gown.Leanne, come on. Let's go.
Let's get you out of here.

07:13.911 --> 07:17.828
Dr. Dixon, status update.Negative FAST, drawing labs,
then we'll send up to CT.

07:17.872 --> 07:21.832
Good. What's going on here?Sutures are in.
Bleeding has stopped.

07:21.876 --> 07:24.705
So when were you gonna tell me
about this OB program?

07:24.748 --> 07:27.011
When I had something to tell.

07:27.055 --> 07:29.274
-It's just an interview.
-Diego, I got this.

07:29.318 --> 07:31.929
But, uh, you wanna be an OB?

07:31.973 --> 07:33.540
I don't know. Possibly.

07:33.583 --> 07:36.281
Okay. Why don't you take
my pregnant patient?

07:36.325 --> 07:38.588
Wait, what about this guy?

07:38.632 --> 07:41.373
You can take him upstairs.
Get him to CT.[ Gloves snap ]

07:41.417 --> 07:44.028
♪♪

07:44.072 --> 07:45.987
You cut through three of
your flexor tendons.

07:46.030 --> 07:48.250
-How'd this happen?
-Punched a window.

07:48.293 --> 07:51.166
-Yeah? Why'd you do that?
-Ah, it was looking at me funny.

07:51.209 --> 07:53.298
Well, you're gonna have to see
a hand surgeon sometime

07:53.342 --> 07:56.650
in the next two or three weeks.
-Ah, I'm fine.

07:56.693 --> 07:58.042
I got another hand.

07:58.086 --> 08:00.218
Besides, I'm trying to fly
under the radar.

08:00.262 --> 08:02.438
Don't want this to screw up
my next tour.

08:02.482 --> 08:04.527
I'm supposed to ship out
in a few weeks.

08:04.571 --> 08:07.312
-How many tours?
-This will be three.

08:07.356 --> 08:10.185
Two was enough for me.

08:10.228 --> 08:13.275
Rather die a hero
than a bum.

08:13.318 --> 08:15.190
I'd rather not die at all.

08:15.233 --> 08:18.367
Well, everybody dies.

08:18.410 --> 08:21.022
[ Sighs ] Come on. You gonna
keep this quiet or...

08:21.065 --> 08:23.938
It's none of my business.

08:23.981 --> 08:27.332
That's a cool tat.
Whose idea was that?

08:27.376 --> 08:29.509
My brother's.

08:29.552 --> 08:32.381
I got the same one.

08:32.424 --> 08:34.992
Well, thanks, buddy.
I owe you one.

08:35.036 --> 08:36.341
Sure.

08:36.385 --> 08:37.778
No, seriously.
If you need anything...

08:37.821 --> 08:40.084
The only thing I need
right now is a key

08:40.128 --> 08:43.044
to the radiology reading room.
-For what?

08:43.087 --> 08:46.961
There's some scans
I need to look at.

08:47.004 --> 08:49.572
They probably got those
on the computer, though, right?

08:49.616 --> 08:51.443
Yeah.

08:51.487 --> 08:54.664
Well,
this is your lucky day.

08:54.708 --> 08:56.840
♪♪

08:56.884 --> 08:59.669
I'm sorry they paged you.I thought a distraction
would be helpful.

08:59.713 --> 09:02.890
[ Exhales sharply ] I can't
seem to do anything, Will.

09:02.933 --> 09:06.067
Are you sure that Emily
hasn't heard from her?

09:06.110 --> 09:08.069
I asked her.
She hasn't heard a word.

09:08.112 --> 09:09.679
Well, maybe I should ask her
myself. Maybe she's covering.

09:09.723 --> 09:11.551
-She doesn't know anything.
-You don't know that!

09:11.594 --> 09:13.204
[ Door closes ]I should ask her myself.

09:13.248 --> 09:16.338
-What?
-We're your friends.

09:16.381 --> 09:18.383
Don't turn us into enemies.

09:18.427 --> 09:21.299
I don't know if she's hurt.
I don't know if she's scared.

09:21.343 --> 09:23.432
I don't know if she's alive.

09:23.475 --> 09:25.826
She is. The police
will find her.

09:25.869 --> 09:27.871
I know it.

09:27.915 --> 09:29.960
Your baby's heart rate
is strong and steady.

09:30.004 --> 09:32.441
-Oh, thank God.
-How does your leg feel?

09:32.484 --> 09:33.964
We can give you some meds
for the pain.

09:34.008 --> 09:35.749
No, I don't want anything
that'll affect my baby girl.

09:35.792 --> 09:38.099
Well, she'll feel a little
sleepy, just like you.

09:38.142 --> 09:40.405
But if you're in pain, that
causes stress on your body,

09:40.449 --> 09:43.104
and she can feel that, too.
We'll do whatever you want.

09:43.147 --> 09:47.674
[ Sighs ] Okay.
Um...just a little.

09:47.717 --> 09:49.545
-Keri?
-Dad.

09:49.589 --> 09:53.288
-Are you okay?
-I'm fine. Baby's fine.

09:53.331 --> 09:54.724
You were all alone?

09:54.768 --> 09:58.119
No, I was with 400
of my closest students.

09:58.162 --> 09:59.599
But nobody with you.

09:59.642 --> 10:01.513
See, you need someone
to take care of you.

10:01.557 --> 10:04.778
Mom, you are going to make this
about me not being married?

10:04.821 --> 10:06.954
Do you really think a husband
could've stopped a stage

10:06.997 --> 10:09.260
from falling on me?
-She didn't say that.

10:09.304 --> 10:11.088
"Why couldn't you just marry
a nice man

10:11.132 --> 10:13.874
instead of starting a family
with a freezer pop?"

10:13.917 --> 10:16.441
Don't be crass.What's wrong with doing things
the old fashioned way?

10:16.485 --> 10:19.357
I was tired of waiting
for someone else

10:19.401 --> 10:23.187
to make my best life.
I can make it myself.

10:23.231 --> 10:26.626
[ Sighs ]
Wecan make it ourselves.

10:26.669 --> 10:29.585
[ Inhales deeply ]

10:29.629 --> 10:31.108
I just think it's...

10:31.152 --> 10:33.502
You ready for surgery,
Ms. Markwith?

10:33.545 --> 10:36.940
I was, but my daughter Tabitha
has been doing some research.

10:36.984 --> 10:40.335
I have. Actually, is the
neurosurgeon available to speak?

10:40.378 --> 10:43.512
We could see if he has
a minute to go --I can answer some questions.

10:43.555 --> 10:47.516
Okay, um, the awake surgery
seems risky.

10:47.559 --> 10:50.650
Yeah, um, all surgeries do
come with some risk.

10:50.693 --> 10:52.303
-What about chemo?
-Chemo is effective,

10:52.347 --> 10:54.131
but it won't repair
your mother's motor function.

10:54.175 --> 10:57.134
And I can't play the piano
without my motor function.

10:57.178 --> 10:59.006
This is about the piano?

10:59.049 --> 11:00.921
You know how much
it means to me.

11:00.964 --> 11:02.705
This surgery is incredible.

11:02.749 --> 11:05.186
Your mother will
actually be conscious,

11:05.229 --> 11:06.927
playing the piano so that
the neurosurgeon knows

11:06.970 --> 11:09.494
exactly what areas
of the brain to avoid.

11:09.538 --> 11:11.192
All right, look,
no offense, Doctor,

11:11.235 --> 11:14.717
that sounds cool, but that's
not what I asked.Tabitha.

11:14.761 --> 11:18.634
I'll be fine.I would rather you be able to
play with your grandkids

11:18.678 --> 11:20.462
than play the piano.

11:20.505 --> 11:23.204
-I'll be able to do both.
-You don't know that.

11:23.247 --> 11:25.032
[ Exhales deeply ]

11:25.075 --> 11:26.729
[ Monitor beeping steadily,
telephone ringing in distance ]

11:26.773 --> 11:28.949
Doctor, could you please let
the neurosurgeon know that

11:28.992 --> 11:31.734
we need to consult
with him again?

11:31.778 --> 11:35.607
Sure.

11:35.651 --> 11:37.958
[ Groaning ]Okay. All right, all right,
all right. Okay, okay.

11:38.001 --> 11:40.221
-Where does it hurt?
-It's my head. It's killing me.

11:40.264 --> 11:41.657
All right, all right,
let me take a look.

11:41.701 --> 11:44.268
All right, you have
a septal hematoma.

11:44.312 --> 11:46.314
-Use a 15 blade.
-Wait, what?

11:46.357 --> 11:48.359
It's a mass of blood
in the membrane

11:48.403 --> 11:50.057
between your nostrils.
We're gonna have to drain it.[ Drawer closes ]

11:50.100 --> 11:52.886
Dr. Avila, I'm gonna need you
to insert the scalpel

11:52.929 --> 11:56.150
in the nostril slowly.
Be careful of the pressure.

11:56.193 --> 11:58.065
-Ah!
-Damn it.

11:58.108 --> 11:59.980
Easy now, easy.
That's too much pressure.

12:00.023 --> 12:02.373
You sure he knows
what he's doing?Moving's gonna make it worse.

12:02.417 --> 12:04.419
Are you seriously blaming me?Bro, I've got a scalpel
in your face right now.

12:04.462 --> 12:06.203
Just calm down.All right, we're gonna have
to stop this bleeding.

12:06.247 --> 12:08.728
Let's get some more
four by fours, please.

12:08.771 --> 12:10.338
-[ Grunts ]
-Damn it.

12:10.381 --> 12:12.209
[ Grunts ]

12:12.253 --> 12:14.429
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:14.472 --> 12:15.691
What are you doing here?

12:15.735 --> 12:17.780
We're in and out of meetings
all day.

12:17.824 --> 12:21.784
Looks like I picked
the wrong time for a tour.Dr. Avila. Now.

12:21.828 --> 12:23.786
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

12:23.830 --> 12:27.094
Join me for lunch
when you're done.

12:27.137 --> 12:29.183
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

12:29.226 --> 12:31.794
[ Typing ]

12:31.838 --> 12:34.405
-Unbelievable.
-What? She's all better?

12:34.449 --> 12:37.191
Well, the swelling has
gone down considerably.

12:37.234 --> 12:40.020
It's time to get her
out of that coma.

12:40.063 --> 12:42.326
But the other guy
doesn't want to.He's wrong.

12:43.850 --> 12:45.286
I'm gonna wake her up
myself.

12:45.329 --> 12:48.245
Cool. How can I help?

12:48.289 --> 12:50.465
[ Knock on door ]

12:50.508 --> 12:53.642
[ Door creaks ]

12:53.685 --> 12:57.211
-Leanne. Hi.
-Owen. I'm sorry to bother you.

12:57.254 --> 12:59.996
I'm sorry I didn't
call you back.

13:00.040 --> 13:02.085
Ariel's missing.

13:02.129 --> 13:03.304
Missing?

13:03.347 --> 13:06.176
She ran away, we think.
I don't know.

13:06.220 --> 13:07.699
I'm grasping at straws.

13:07.743 --> 13:12.313
I was hoping maybe I could
look at Max's phone.

13:12.356 --> 13:15.142
Maybe there'd be something
in his texts with Ariel,

13:15.185 --> 13:18.362
something that would help me
figure out where she is.

13:18.406 --> 13:21.975
I wanna help, Leanne.
I do. But I...do.

13:22.018 --> 13:23.672
I know
this is a difficult time.

13:23.715 --> 13:28.242
I haven't even been into
his room since he, uh...

13:28.285 --> 13:30.287
I'm just not ready.

13:30.331 --> 13:34.161
I understand.
But she's out there somewhere.

13:34.204 --> 13:37.338
Well, she'll come back.

13:39.906 --> 13:41.429
Of course.

13:41.472 --> 13:43.823
I'm so sorry.

13:47.739 --> 13:50.003
Leanne.

13:50.046 --> 13:51.874
Wait.

13:51.918 --> 13:52.875
♪♪

14:02.798 --> 14:05.845
I should offer you
some coffee or something.

14:08.282 --> 14:10.458
-Do you want coffee?
-No.

14:10.501 --> 14:13.243
[ Chuckles ]

14:13.287 --> 14:16.856
-I-I just can't seem to...
-I know.

14:16.899 --> 14:19.510
Why don't I get the phone?

14:22.296 --> 14:24.864
Best hot dogs in the city.I don't think a lot of people
share that opinion.

14:24.907 --> 14:27.083
Your mom and I used to
sneak in here for these things.

14:27.127 --> 14:29.607
My first gig,
3 bucks an hour

14:29.651 --> 14:32.393
driving around for that
slumlord, Jim Mead.

14:32.436 --> 14:34.047
Any building
on a decent block

14:34.090 --> 14:37.093
with at least two broken
windows, he bought it.

14:37.137 --> 14:38.703
Yeah,
I know the story, Dad.

14:38.747 --> 14:41.097
When the bubble burst, Jim Mead
was so far upside down,

14:41.141 --> 14:42.664
he couldn't find the floor.

14:42.707 --> 14:45.275
I bought him out
pennies on the dollar.

14:45.319 --> 14:46.886
You know, I showed
the documentary

14:46.929 --> 14:48.931
to a professor from one
of my old film classes.

14:48.975 --> 14:50.933
He loved it.
He's Oscar-nominated.

14:50.977 --> 14:53.283
I'm not. I'm just trying to do
what's right for this hospital.

14:53.327 --> 14:56.765
Your movie makes this place
look risky.But we save lives.

14:56.808 --> 14:57.940
That's the whole point
of the film.

14:57.984 --> 15:00.116
I'm shutting it down.

15:00.160 --> 15:02.075
-No, you can't do that.
-It's my money.

15:02.118 --> 15:03.946
Why would you even let me
do it in the first place

15:03.990 --> 15:06.296
if you're just gonna do this?
-You asked.

15:06.340 --> 15:09.604
I was hoping you'd surprise me,
but as usual,

15:09.647 --> 15:11.606
you didn't have
the follow-through.

15:11.649 --> 15:15.175
Fries could be better.

15:15.218 --> 15:16.959
♪♪

15:17.003 --> 15:18.961
[ Indistinct conversations,
siren wailing in distance ]

15:19.005 --> 15:20.441
Another one from
the stage collapse?

15:20.484 --> 15:21.790
She was trapped for hours.
They just found her.

15:21.833 --> 15:24.227
-BP's 70 over 40.
-What happened to her?

15:24.271 --> 15:26.621
Is she okay?!

15:26.664 --> 15:28.753
Is she okay?

15:28.797 --> 15:31.756
Hang another liter of NS
and give me the ultrasound.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.193
Right away.

15:33.236 --> 15:35.369
-Here you go.
-Gloves.

15:35.412 --> 15:38.633
-All right, what do you see?
-Sternal fracture

15:38.676 --> 15:41.505
with a fluid collection
compressing the heart.Retrosternal hematoma.

15:41.549 --> 15:43.377
She needs the OR,
but right now,

15:43.420 --> 15:45.509
it's causing
tamponade physiology.

15:45.553 --> 15:48.425
Jesse, give me an 18 gauge
long needle and 20cc syringe.

15:48.469 --> 15:50.514
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]Pressure's dropping.

15:50.558 --> 15:53.648
-Push 1 epi.
-Coding, Dr. Savetti.

15:53.691 --> 15:55.563
You want compressions?No, she needs a needle
decompression now.

15:55.606 --> 15:59.175
Okay, slow down,
watch the monitor.[ Whooshing ]

15:59.219 --> 16:01.482
We need to maneuver
the needle right --I'm in.

16:01.525 --> 16:03.701
All right, then.

16:03.745 --> 16:06.356
Okay, pressure's coming up.

16:06.400 --> 16:08.315
Heart rate's improving.

16:08.358 --> 16:09.925
Let's get her up to surgery.

16:09.969 --> 16:12.319
Let's go.

16:12.362 --> 16:15.887
♪♪

16:15.931 --> 16:17.715
What?

16:17.759 --> 16:19.979
Just proud of you,
that's all.

16:20.022 --> 16:23.721
♪♪

16:23.765 --> 16:26.855
Logan. Logan, come on.
Come on, relax. Relax, okay.[ Gasping ]

16:26.898 --> 16:29.466
-That woman! Is she okay?
-Who?

16:29.510 --> 16:31.468
-I don't know her name.
-Okay, heart rate is 140.

16:31.512 --> 16:33.383
Dr. Avila, let's push
1 of ativan.

16:33.427 --> 16:36.430
You should start to feel better
right about...

16:36.473 --> 16:38.084
now.

16:38.127 --> 16:41.043
-Okay.
-[ Exhales deeply ]

16:41.087 --> 16:43.915
Now you wanna tell us
what that was about?Nothing.

16:43.959 --> 16:47.571
People don't usually have
panic attacks for no reason.

16:47.615 --> 16:48.920
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

16:48.964 --> 16:52.837
When the stage went down,
I panicked.

16:52.881 --> 16:56.493
I ran.Well, it sounds like that's
what everybody did.

16:56.537 --> 16:59.409
You don't get it. I ran.
I...pushed.

16:59.453 --> 17:02.847
I pushed her out of my way.

17:02.891 --> 17:05.937
I'm an offensive lineman.

17:05.981 --> 17:08.810
I'm on scholarship
for one reason --

17:08.853 --> 17:12.074
To protect people.
[ Scoffs ]

17:12.118 --> 17:14.076
But in real life,
when push came to shove --

17:14.120 --> 17:16.165
-You pushed and you shoved.
-Dr. Avila.

17:16.209 --> 17:18.298
That's literally what he did.No one knows how any of us
would react

17:18.341 --> 17:21.518
in the same situation.
Point is, it's not your fault

17:21.562 --> 17:23.738
that that woman got hurt.
-Yes, it is.

17:23.781 --> 17:25.957
That's enough, Dr. Avila.

17:26.001 --> 17:27.307
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

17:27.350 --> 17:30.745
Now, Logan, I want you
to get some rest, okay?

17:30.788 --> 17:32.616
You've had a tough day.

17:32.660 --> 17:35.184
Dr. Avila, a word, please.

17:35.228 --> 17:38.100
[ Monitor beeping steadily,
telephone ringing in distance ]

17:38.144 --> 17:40.189
You wanna tell me what
you're doing in there?

17:40.233 --> 17:43.062
I'm just telling the truth.No. No, you're angry.
That's the truth.

17:43.105 --> 17:45.847
The board saw your movie,
and they didn't like it.

17:45.890 --> 17:47.457
You think I care
what they think?

17:47.501 --> 17:49.285
You care what
your father thinks.

17:49.329 --> 17:54.116
♪♪

17:54.160 --> 17:56.510
[ Monitor beeping rapidly,
curtain rings swoosh ]Dr. Kean, what's going on?

17:56.553 --> 17:59.556
You feel hot. I think
you have a fever. Any pain?

17:59.600 --> 18:01.123
-Not really.
-Where are your parents?

18:01.167 --> 18:04.083
They were driving me crazy.
I sent them for coffee. Why?

18:04.126 --> 18:06.824
Is it bad?Listen, Keri, I'm gonna
figure this out,

18:06.868 --> 18:08.913
but I need to check to see
if your water broke.

18:08.957 --> 18:11.133
You're doing great. You're gonna
feel a little pressure.

18:11.177 --> 18:12.569
-[ Groans ]
-Hey.

18:12.613 --> 18:14.397
-Possible infection.
-Did you increase fluids?

18:14.441 --> 18:16.834
-She's on her third liter.
-Hey. Deep breaths.

18:16.878 --> 18:19.272
Do you have a name
picked out yet?

18:19.315 --> 18:21.230
I do. But you're gonna laugh.

18:21.274 --> 18:23.841
I'm a girl named Noa.
Try me.

18:23.885 --> 18:27.323
-Peregrine.
-Wow.

18:27.367 --> 18:29.456
I know it's crazy,
but it's a family name,

18:29.499 --> 18:31.806
and I sort of love it.

18:31.849 --> 18:34.025
It's beautiful.

18:34.069 --> 18:35.549
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

18:35.592 --> 18:37.333
-Ferning.
-Mm-hmm.

18:37.377 --> 18:39.335
That tells me that this is
amniotic fluid

18:39.379 --> 18:40.989
and your water did break.

18:41.032 --> 18:42.425
So we need to start you
on antibiotics and fluids

18:42.469 --> 18:44.862
and deliver this baby sooner
rather than later.

18:44.906 --> 18:48.518
But is she okay?She's fine. She's just...
ready to meet you.

18:48.562 --> 18:50.303
I'll go find your parents
and let 'em know.

18:50.346 --> 18:53.697
Good. It's just another reason
for my mom to say I told you so.

18:53.741 --> 18:58.311
She's gonna be a grandma.
She'll be thrilled.

18:58.354 --> 18:59.747
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:59.790 --> 19:01.183
So you consulted
with the surgeon,

19:01.227 --> 19:03.098
I hear you're still
trying to decide.

19:03.142 --> 19:04.882
My daughter thinks
it's just too risky

19:04.926 --> 19:09.409
and chemo is less invasive.
-Well, she's right, actually.

19:09.452 --> 19:11.062
You're scared, and I get it.

19:11.106 --> 19:14.196
My brother was in a coma
last year, and I was alone,

19:14.240 --> 19:16.024
fighting with everyone
in the room

19:16.067 --> 19:18.244
because they wanted to be safe.

19:18.287 --> 19:20.507
But I chose the aggressive
course, and I was right.

19:20.550 --> 19:22.204
You mean you were lucky.

19:22.248 --> 19:24.032
Least with chemo, we know
exactly what we're getting.

19:24.075 --> 19:26.208
There are minimal downsides
to surgery.

19:26.252 --> 19:28.079
We can repair
your mother's brain.

19:28.123 --> 19:31.039
She'll still be her, and her
gift will still be intact.

19:31.082 --> 19:34.085
You can't say that for sure.But with chemo, we can only
shrink the tumor.

19:34.129 --> 19:36.392
We cannot give her back
her ability to play.

19:36.436 --> 19:38.655
Honey, that's really
important to me.

19:38.699 --> 19:40.004
I feel lost without
being able to play.

19:40.048 --> 19:41.658
I don't care about that.

19:41.702 --> 19:44.008
To me, you're not the great
and talented Vicky Markwith.

19:44.052 --> 19:47.316
You're my mom.This isn't about emotion.
This is science.

19:47.360 --> 19:50.580
20 years ago, we couldn't cure
your mother, but now we can.

19:50.624 --> 19:52.930
We can give her everything
she wants.

19:52.974 --> 19:55.585
With chemo, you are dooming
your mother's chance

19:55.629 --> 19:57.892
to ever play the piano again.

19:57.935 --> 20:00.677
But with this surgery,
she will have it all.

20:00.721 --> 20:03.941
Sweetheart, I'm gonna try.

20:03.985 --> 20:06.030
Oh. [ Sighs ]

20:06.074 --> 20:08.946
See you in there.

20:08.990 --> 20:11.297
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:11.340 --> 20:14.256
I'm sorry, minimal downsides
to removing a brain tumor?

20:14.300 --> 20:16.040
Chemotherapy isn't a cure.

20:16.084 --> 20:18.260
What if someone took away
your ability to be a doctor?

20:18.304 --> 20:19.783
I would rather spend time
with my family

20:19.827 --> 20:21.220
than take a risk like this.

20:21.263 --> 20:23.439
Well, you're not me or her.
It's what she wants.

20:23.483 --> 20:26.616
Because youconvinced her.I helped my patient make
the right choice.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.139
Angus...

20:28.183 --> 20:31.926
♪♪

20:31.969 --> 20:35.146
[ Dog barking in distance ]

20:35.190 --> 20:38.628
-Are you sure you're okay?
-Yeah, yeah.

20:38.672 --> 20:40.587
Sort of.

20:40.630 --> 20:43.807
Maybe it'd be better
if we just said it out loud.

20:43.851 --> 20:47.811
I'll be Max,
and you do Ariel.

20:47.855 --> 20:49.422
That's better?

20:49.465 --> 20:53.513
I don't know. I mean,
it can't be any worse.

20:53.556 --> 20:59.301
Uh, there.Okay, uh, "roflamayo." I have
no idea what that means.

20:59.345 --> 21:02.304
R-O-F-L-M-A-O. Everybody
knows what that means.

21:02.348 --> 21:07.309
Oh. Um, well, try again.
Into character.

21:07.353 --> 21:09.920
"How's it going over
in Siberia?"

21:09.964 --> 21:13.184
"Freezing. Duh."
Icicle emoji.

21:13.228 --> 21:16.100
-"How about Antarctica?"
-"Warm. Very warm."

21:16.144 --> 21:19.843
"#globalwarmingisreal."
Crying face emoji.

21:19.887 --> 21:22.193
Huh. [ Chuckles ]

21:22.237 --> 21:23.630
He was funny.

21:23.673 --> 21:26.502
He was. You okay?

21:26.546 --> 21:28.852
Let's keep going.

21:28.896 --> 21:30.811
Uh...

21:30.854 --> 21:34.031
"T-B-H. Low-key nervous."

21:34.075 --> 21:35.598
"It's a house party.

21:35.642 --> 21:38.340
Everyone's super chill.
Joy's the best."

21:38.384 --> 21:41.517
"Joy's boyfriend is,
like, 30,

21:41.561 --> 21:44.041
"and he carries a knife?

21:44.085 --> 21:47.175
Joy's totes sketch.
Emily seems to think so, too."

21:47.218 --> 21:49.395
-What? Who's Joy?
-I have no idea.

21:49.438 --> 21:51.788
Keep going. "Emily's going."
What -- and then it stops.

21:51.832 --> 21:53.137
That's it.

21:53.181 --> 21:57.185
♪♪

21:57.228 --> 22:00.231
You're gonna be fine.

22:00.275 --> 22:01.711
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

22:01.755 --> 22:03.060
It's time to wake up.

22:03.104 --> 22:04.888
So this surgeon is
a one-star general

22:04.932 --> 22:06.803
you flew halfway
across the state to see...[ Beeps ]

22:06.847 --> 22:09.023
and now you're saying
he's all wrong.

22:09.066 --> 22:10.807
Just trying to save my friend.

22:10.851 --> 22:12.374
Your friend?

22:12.418 --> 22:14.071
What's that supposed to mean?

22:14.115 --> 22:15.725
Do you love her?

22:15.769 --> 22:20.251
I'm gonna take that
as a yes.

22:20.295 --> 22:21.557
When's she supposed
to wake up?

22:21.601 --> 22:23.124
Soon.

22:23.167 --> 22:25.735
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]What happened?

22:25.779 --> 22:27.563
I don't know.

22:27.607 --> 22:29.391
Well, you don't have much time.
Somebody had to have heard that.

22:29.435 --> 22:31.219
She doesn't need much time.
Just a few more minutes,

22:31.262 --> 22:32.829
and she's gonna be able
to breathe on her own.[ Gasps ]

22:32.873 --> 22:34.527
-Damn it.
-What?

22:34.570 --> 22:36.398
-There's an obstruction.
-Sounds bad.

22:36.442 --> 22:38.574
It's okay. It's just being on
the vent too long.

22:38.618 --> 22:41.795
Her pneumonia's worse.
It's okay, it's okay.

22:41.838 --> 22:45.189
-Just mucus in the tube.
-She doesn't look okay.

22:45.233 --> 22:47.757
You know that nurse is gonna
call on the cavalry.

22:47.801 --> 22:50.107
I don't care who she calls.

22:50.151 --> 22:52.109
No breath sounds on the left.

22:52.153 --> 22:54.808
-You gotta call for help.
-I don't need any help.

22:54.851 --> 22:57.767
She popped a lung.
That's what happens when
infections get out of hand.

22:57.811 --> 23:01.815
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

23:05.166 --> 23:07.081
Step away from my patient.

23:07.124 --> 23:09.039
I would, General, but my
finger's keeping her lung open.

23:09.083 --> 23:11.259
You wanna glove up and help me
put in this chest tube?

23:11.302 --> 23:13.870
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

23:13.914 --> 23:15.437
[ Sighs ]

23:15.481 --> 23:16.482
♪♪

23:22.488 --> 23:25.665
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

23:25.708 --> 23:27.057
Hand me the tube, please.

23:27.101 --> 23:28.407
Make sure you clamp
the distal end.

23:28.450 --> 23:30.757
This is my 7,000th chest tube.
I got it.

23:30.800 --> 23:33.150
You're awfully cocky
for a guy who just
caused a collapsed lung.

23:33.194 --> 23:34.543
You caused this by keeping her
on the vent too long.

23:34.587 --> 23:36.153
You don't know that.

23:36.197 --> 23:37.633
I told you, this is
my 7,000th chest tube.

23:37.677 --> 23:39.461
I know what I'm doing,
and I know what happened.

23:39.505 --> 23:41.550
And I know you better extubate
her when we're through here.

23:41.594 --> 23:43.900
Don't put her back on sedation
just to spite me.

23:43.944 --> 23:46.686
I don't treat patients
out of spite.

23:46.729 --> 23:49.776
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]Now step away
from my patient.

23:49.819 --> 23:51.342
Are you gonna extubate her?

23:51.386 --> 23:54.345
I've given you an order,
Colonel. Now step off.

23:54.389 --> 24:00.308
♪♪

24:00.351 --> 24:03.833
[ Gloves snap ]

24:03.877 --> 24:05.487
♪♪

24:05.531 --> 24:10.144
Enough with the opening act,
time for the headliner. Nurse.

24:10.187 --> 24:12.015
[ Click ]

24:12.059 --> 24:14.801
Okay, Vicky, Dr. Edlen's gonna
start to remove your tumor now.

24:14.844 --> 24:17.194
Any requests?

24:17.238 --> 24:19.719
-Debussy?
-Man after my own heart.

24:19.762 --> 24:22.591
-"Reverie"?
-Deep cut. I love it.

24:22.635 --> 24:27.117
[ Playing "Reverie" ]

24:27.161 --> 24:28.554
[ Crackles ]

24:28.597 --> 24:30.860
Have you ever heard her
play before?
Nope.

24:30.904 --> 24:33.297
♪♪

24:33.341 --> 24:37.171
My husband had a box at
the Phil for five seasons.

24:37.214 --> 24:39.434
Her Schumann
"Concerto in A Minor"

24:39.478 --> 24:41.610
is the only performance
we've ever agreed on.

24:41.654 --> 24:42.829
[ Sizzle]

24:42.872 --> 24:45.179
♪♪

24:45.222 --> 24:46.659
It's beautiful.

24:46.702 --> 24:47.790
[ Sizzle ]

24:47.834 --> 24:49.705
[ Plays discordant note ]Freeze.

24:49.749 --> 24:54.057
What happened?Ah, we poked where we
should've prodded.

24:54.101 --> 24:57.452
Don't move out of the field.

24:57.496 --> 24:59.802
Okay, Vicky, can you
pick it up from there?

24:59.846 --> 25:02.675
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

25:02.718 --> 25:04.546
[ Resumes playing ]

25:04.590 --> 25:06.635
Thattagirl.

25:06.679 --> 25:08.594
[ Sizzling ]

25:08.637 --> 25:09.725
♪♪

25:09.769 --> 25:11.553
Hmm. Steady hands.

25:11.597 --> 25:13.903
So what year are you?

25:13.947 --> 25:15.731
Third year.

25:15.775 --> 25:19.430
Well, first year. I just
switched into surgery.

25:19.474 --> 25:22.564
I'll be sure Dr. Campbell
knows he trained you well.

25:22.608 --> 25:28.048
♪♪

25:28.091 --> 25:30.790
[ Sizzling ]

25:30.833 --> 25:32.531
Just like I told my dad,

25:32.574 --> 25:35.751
I haven't heard from Ariel
in a week, and I don't know Joy.

25:35.795 --> 25:39.233
According to Max,
you do know Joy.

25:39.276 --> 25:40.756
Emily.

25:40.800 --> 25:43.019
I know you wanna
protect Ariel,

25:43.063 --> 25:46.414
but that's my job.
I'm her mother.

25:46.457 --> 25:48.895
No matter what else happens,
no matter how short a time

25:48.938 --> 25:51.375
we've been in
each other's lives,

25:51.419 --> 25:54.465
I'm her mother.

25:54.509 --> 25:57.120
I need her
to be home with me.

25:57.164 --> 26:00.428
I need her to be safe.

26:00.471 --> 26:04.650
It's my job to help
with she's going through.

26:04.693 --> 26:07.609
It's my job to hold her
and to tell her that

26:07.653 --> 26:10.133
everything's gonna be okay.

26:10.177 --> 26:13.702
And I really, really need
to tell her that.

26:13.746 --> 26:16.923
And frankly, I need her
to tell me that, too.

26:16.966 --> 26:20.970
♪♪

26:21.014 --> 26:22.624
She told me not to tell.

26:22.668 --> 26:25.627
-Is she with Joy?
-Yes.

26:25.671 --> 26:27.498
Where does Joy live?

26:27.542 --> 26:29.892
Nowhere. She was
in foster care like Ariel,

26:29.936 --> 26:31.328
but it didn't work out.

26:31.372 --> 26:34.157
That's probably why Ariel
gravitated to her.

26:34.201 --> 26:36.116
If she doesn't have a home,
where does she stay?

26:36.159 --> 26:37.421
Joy and some other kids --

26:37.465 --> 26:40.773
they crash in different places
around town.

26:40.816 --> 26:42.644
I think I remember Ariel
saying something

26:42.688 --> 26:44.646
about
the 8th Street Bridge.

26:44.690 --> 26:47.170
That's near Angels.

26:47.214 --> 26:51.261
Emily, you're a good friend.

26:51.305 --> 26:54.047
You did the right thing by
telling us where she was.

26:54.090 --> 26:57.659
But you're grounded...
till college.

26:57.703 --> 27:01.794
[ Sighs ]

27:01.837 --> 27:05.841
[ Woman speaks indistinctly
over P.A. ]

27:05.885 --> 27:07.060
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

27:07.103 --> 27:08.931
Dr. Kean, right?

27:08.975 --> 27:11.368
Right.
Are you looking for Diego?

27:11.412 --> 27:14.154
-I can have him paged.
-Oh, that's all right.

27:14.197 --> 27:17.113
If you see him, just tell him
I said goodbye.

27:17.157 --> 27:20.551
Sure. And, uh, listen,

27:20.595 --> 27:22.118
thanks for making that call.

27:22.162 --> 27:25.034
Or having your assistant
do it.

27:25.078 --> 27:27.384
No trouble. Literally.

27:29.735 --> 27:32.563
But how about I do you
a real favor?

27:32.607 --> 27:34.174
That's not necessary.

27:34.217 --> 27:37.873
-What's not necessary?
-We're all having dinner.

27:37.917 --> 27:39.353
We help Dr. Jean prepare
for her interview,

27:39.396 --> 27:41.311
and I get to pick her brain

27:41.355 --> 27:43.052
about how you're really
doing here.

27:43.096 --> 27:45.402
-I'm doing fine here.
-He is.

27:45.446 --> 27:47.796
Well, I hope
you'll consider it.

27:47.840 --> 27:49.885
I know everybody
at that hospital,

27:49.929 --> 27:54.368
and most of them owe me one.
Diego, always a pleasure.

27:54.411 --> 27:56.065
[ Door opens ]

27:56.109 --> 27:58.415
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

27:58.459 --> 28:00.026
-He's, uh...
-A douche?

28:00.069 --> 28:04.247
Yeah. It's his best quality.

28:04.291 --> 28:07.990
♪♪

28:08.034 --> 28:10.514
-Dr. Savetti.
-You're leaving?

28:10.558 --> 28:12.429
I have a personal situation
to deal with,

28:12.473 --> 28:14.780
but the hospital's
in good hands.

28:14.823 --> 28:18.392
I watched you today.
You were tested.

28:18.435 --> 28:22.875
See, you could've shied
away from the challenge,

28:22.918 --> 28:24.833
but you demanded the ball,

28:24.877 --> 28:26.705
and you didn't let
your team down.

28:26.748 --> 28:29.577
Thanks, I, uh, appreciate that.

28:29.620 --> 28:31.187
The job's yours
if you want it.

28:31.231 --> 28:34.277
-The attending spot?
-Dr. Savetti, catch up.

28:34.321 --> 28:36.279
There's somewhere I need to be.
Accept it or don't.

28:36.323 --> 28:38.586
-I want it.
-There you go.

28:38.629 --> 28:40.457
♪♪

28:40.501 --> 28:43.417
[ Exhales, grunts ]

28:43.460 --> 28:44.853
[ Grunts ]

28:44.897 --> 28:47.377
-Hey, sorry.
-Yeah.

28:47.421 --> 28:49.771
Yes!

28:49.815 --> 28:52.818
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

28:52.861 --> 28:55.255
-What's going on?
-There's something wrong.

28:55.298 --> 28:57.126
-She's found some trees.
-I'm afraid your mother

28:57.170 --> 28:58.867
is suffering
from receptive aphasia.

28:58.911 --> 29:00.564
It's a form of language
impairment that affects

29:00.608 --> 29:04.351
the production of speech.
-Well, how long's it last?

29:04.394 --> 29:06.048
If she works with
a speech therapist,

29:06.092 --> 29:10.009
it couldimprove.
-But there are no guarantees.

29:10.052 --> 29:14.796
No. That is not
what he said.

29:14.840 --> 29:16.406
He said there was
no downside!

29:16.450 --> 29:18.495
With the paintings, they --
they -- they thank us.

29:18.539 --> 29:21.020
You made me believe!

29:21.063 --> 29:22.456
We would've never agreed
to the surgery

29:22.499 --> 29:24.240
if we understood what
we could lose.

29:24.284 --> 29:26.416
Dr. Leighton, what exactly
did you tell her?

29:26.460 --> 29:31.334
♪♪

29:31.378 --> 29:33.510
You put her at risk of
worsening brain hemorrhaging,

29:33.554 --> 29:36.339
swelling --I saved her life and you'll know
it, too, when she wakes up.

29:36.383 --> 29:38.472
Ifshe wakes up.
Colonel Willis,
I'm placing you under arrest.

29:38.515 --> 29:42.389
What?You violated a direct order
and endangered a patient.

29:42.432 --> 29:44.217
Get off me!You're making a big mistake.
[ Handcuffs clink ]

29:44.260 --> 29:46.262
Get him outta here.

29:46.306 --> 29:51.267
♪♪

29:51.311 --> 29:52.529
[ Gasps ]

29:52.573 --> 29:54.227
-Dr. Guthrie!
-What happened?

29:54.270 --> 29:56.185
I don't know. He just --
he couldn't catch his breath.

29:56.229 --> 29:57.839
All right, relax.

29:57.883 --> 29:59.362
[ Inhales deeply ]

29:59.406 --> 30:01.408
Decreased breath sounds
on the left.

30:01.451 --> 30:03.192
I repeated his ultrasound
when he started getting worse.Okay, show me.

30:03.236 --> 30:05.804
-Okay.
-[ Wheezing ]

30:05.847 --> 30:08.197
[ Whooshing ]Left-sided pleural effusion.

30:08.241 --> 30:09.503
He had a small one
when he came in,

30:09.546 --> 30:12.158
but now, I mean, it's huge.
-Okay.

30:12.201 --> 30:13.376
What's your next step?

30:13.420 --> 30:14.943
You know.

30:14.987 --> 30:16.771
[ Clears throat ]
A ch-chest tube.

30:16.815 --> 30:18.860
All right. Okay, Logan,
listen to me.

30:18.904 --> 30:20.731
Fluid has collected
around your left lung,

30:20.775 --> 30:23.734
and we're gonna have to insert
a tube to drain it, all right?

30:23.778 --> 30:25.519
-Give him 8 milligrams morphine.
-Just relax. Just relax.

30:25.562 --> 30:29.044
All right.
Remember the anatomy.

30:29.088 --> 30:30.393
Okay.

30:30.437 --> 30:32.134
Mid-axillary line.

30:32.178 --> 30:33.875
Fourth intercostal space.

30:33.919 --> 30:37.183
-Okay. I think I got it.
-There we go.

30:37.226 --> 30:39.663
-What the...
-Okay, step back, step back.

30:39.707 --> 30:41.404
Okay.
Hey, we need help over here!

30:41.448 --> 30:43.232
Coming up.

30:43.276 --> 30:44.930
Dr. Kean, something's wrong.

30:44.973 --> 30:46.845
-[ Wheezing ]
-Keri? What's going on?

30:46.888 --> 30:48.324
[ Strained voice ]
I can't breathe.Mario!

30:48.368 --> 30:50.370
What -- what's happening?

30:50.413 --> 30:51.588
[ Coughing ]

30:51.632 --> 30:53.982
[ Gasping ]

30:54.026 --> 30:57.986
[ Whooshing loudly ]

30:58.030 --> 30:59.553
Lungs are clear.

30:59.596 --> 31:00.684
[ Breathy voice ] Mom.

31:00.728 --> 31:02.599
[ Wheezes ] The baby.

31:02.643 --> 31:03.905
The doctors are taking care
of you, sweetheart.

31:03.949 --> 31:05.602
-Everything will be fine.
-[ Coughs ]

31:05.646 --> 31:08.823
Promise me.Oh, my God.
Is she gonna be okay?

31:08.867 --> 31:11.478
Severely dilated RV,
reduced systolic function.

31:11.521 --> 31:13.697
PE?
Maybe or an amniotic
fluid embolism,

31:13.741 --> 31:15.786
possibly a fat embolism.
-[ Coughs, gasps ]

31:15.830 --> 31:17.963
-Acute heart failure.
-Heart failure?

31:18.006 --> 31:20.922
-Oh, god. Keri.
-Mom.

31:20.966 --> 31:24.186
[ Wheezing ]
Take...care of her.

31:24.230 --> 31:26.145
Youwill take care of her.
You'll be fine.

31:26.188 --> 31:28.756
-Promise her.
-[ Wheezes ]

31:28.799 --> 31:32.629
I promise.Okay, start compressions.
Let's get her to center stage.

31:32.673 --> 31:34.631
Jesse: Starting compressions.
Okay, let's move.

31:34.675 --> 31:35.806
Give her some room, people.

31:35.850 --> 31:36.851
♪♪

31:43.031 --> 31:44.337
This patients needs
a thoracotomy, Dr. Avila.

31:44.380 --> 31:45.729
-You're up.
-No, I've never done one.

31:45.773 --> 31:47.079
Don't worry. You're ready.

31:47.122 --> 31:49.472
You're in
the right atrium.

31:49.516 --> 31:52.258
Try pulling back on the syringe.I'm trying.
There's still nothing.

31:52.301 --> 31:54.695
There's no more time.I know. We have to
save the baby.

31:54.738 --> 31:56.871
We need to do
a crash C-section.

31:56.915 --> 32:00.222
Okay, bleeding is
from the left lung.

32:00.266 --> 32:01.832
Dr. Avila.

32:01.876 --> 32:03.182
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

32:03.225 --> 32:05.053
Listen to me, your problem
is nobody's told you

32:05.097 --> 32:06.750
what you're good at.

32:06.794 --> 32:09.405
Well, I'm telling you now,
you're good.

32:09.449 --> 32:10.929
You can do this.

32:10.972 --> 32:13.844
I've seen your work, son.
Don't give up now.

32:13.888 --> 32:17.065
♪♪

32:17.109 --> 32:20.025
Heavy arterial bleed
from the hilum.Mm-hmm.

32:20.068 --> 32:21.461
-I can't tie it off.
-Yes. Yes, you can.

32:21.504 --> 32:23.854
I-I don't know.
It's too proximal to clamp.

32:23.898 --> 32:26.248
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

32:26.292 --> 32:27.684
Feel it.

32:27.728 --> 32:29.686
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

32:29.730 --> 32:31.340
Yes.

32:31.384 --> 32:33.125
In med school,
I read about this thing.

32:33.168 --> 32:35.127
Can we twist the lung on itself
to cut off the bleeding?

32:35.170 --> 32:36.780
You bet we can.

32:36.824 --> 32:38.782
All right, Dr. Guthrie,
hold the base.Yes.

32:38.826 --> 32:41.655
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

32:41.698 --> 32:43.265
[ Exhales ]
The bleeding stopped.

32:43.309 --> 32:46.529
Yeah. All right, let's get
this patient to the OR.

32:46.573 --> 32:48.401
Good work, son.

32:48.444 --> 32:50.533
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:50.577 --> 32:53.493
Still no pulse.Do not stop compressions.
She needs to see her baby girl.

32:53.536 --> 32:55.190
[ Pounding ]Come on.

32:55.234 --> 32:59.760
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:59.803 --> 33:01.718
-You got this.
-Here she comes.

33:01.762 --> 33:04.852
-That's it.
-Got her.

33:04.895 --> 33:07.289
[ Exhales deeply ]

33:07.333 --> 33:08.987
That's it.

33:09.030 --> 33:10.510
She's not breathing.

33:10.553 --> 33:11.990
We need suction over here!

33:12.033 --> 33:15.645
-Noa, you need help?
-Don't stop compressions.

33:15.689 --> 33:19.127
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:19.171 --> 33:21.825
Come on. Come on.

33:21.869 --> 33:24.567
Come on.

33:24.611 --> 33:26.482
-Come on!
-Come on.

33:26.526 --> 33:27.875
Come on.

33:27.918 --> 33:29.659
♪♪

33:29.703 --> 33:31.444
Come on.

33:31.487 --> 33:34.664
-Come on.
-Come on.

33:34.708 --> 33:39.191
[ Baby crying ]

33:39.234 --> 33:41.149
[ Exhales ]

33:41.193 --> 33:45.327
[ Baby continues crying ]

33:45.371 --> 33:46.763
[ Exhales deeply ]

33:46.807 --> 33:53.031
[ Crying continues ]

33:53.074 --> 33:55.468
[ Exhales deeply ]

33:55.511 --> 33:57.383
[ Crying continues ]

33:57.426 --> 33:59.689
Time of death -- 6:42 p.m.

33:59.733 --> 34:01.865
[ Crying ]

34:01.909 --> 34:05.434
6:42 p.m., same time as birth.

34:05.478 --> 34:10.265
[ Crying ]

34:10.309 --> 34:12.224
All right.

34:12.267 --> 34:15.357
[ Continues crying ]

34:15.401 --> 34:18.578
♪♪

34:18.621 --> 34:25.367
[ Crying continues ]

34:25.411 --> 34:29.806
[ Fusses ]

34:29.850 --> 34:33.332
Rorish: Excuse me. Have you
seen this person? No?

34:33.375 --> 34:35.421
Have you seen this person?

34:35.464 --> 34:38.859
I'm sorry to drag you
into this.

34:38.902 --> 34:40.687
It's okay.
I'm glad I'm here.

34:40.730 --> 34:42.993
Thank you for coming, Mama.

34:43.037 --> 34:45.518
-Hey, guys.
-Have you seen this person?

34:45.561 --> 34:47.128
Jesse and Rorish: No?

34:47.172 --> 34:49.478
Have you seen this person?
Her name is Ariel.

34:49.522 --> 34:51.132
What about someone named Joy?

34:51.176 --> 34:57.095
You know someone named Joy?
Does that ring a bell?

34:57.138 --> 34:58.792
Okay, thanks.

34:58.835 --> 35:03.797
♪♪

35:03.840 --> 35:06.104
Is that water
from over there?

35:06.147 --> 35:08.758
It's a piano, Mom.

35:08.802 --> 35:10.586
-Will they be there?
-Well, it's from pediatrics.

35:10.630 --> 35:12.588
It's not what you're used to,

35:12.632 --> 35:14.938
but the sound quality will be
much better than the keyboard.

35:14.982 --> 35:16.940
And I don't know. I figure that
it would be a good way for you

35:16.984 --> 35:19.334
to express yourself.
-Do you wanna play it.

35:19.378 --> 35:21.031
-I pick the sky.
-Can she walk?

35:21.075 --> 35:23.382
I did.
Yeah, of course,
if she wants to.

35:23.425 --> 35:24.905
Here. Let me help you,
Ms. Markwith.

35:24.948 --> 35:26.863
We'll play together, okay?

35:26.907 --> 35:29.910
Oh. Water.

35:29.953 --> 35:32.042
For the ocean.

35:34.132 --> 35:43.445
[ Playing slow-tempo melody ]

35:43.489 --> 35:46.883
[ Gasps ]

35:46.927 --> 35:48.146
-Tabitha?
-[ Crying ]

35:48.189 --> 35:51.061
She, uh...

35:51.105 --> 35:53.063
♪♪

35:53.107 --> 35:55.196
She wrote this song for me
when I was a baby.

35:55.240 --> 35:57.720
She used to sing it to me
all the time.

35:57.764 --> 36:00.158
For the ocean.

36:00.201 --> 36:01.855
♪♪

36:01.898 --> 36:05.728
I think your mother's asking
for you to sing it to her.

36:05.772 --> 36:10.820
♪♪

36:10.864 --> 36:15.999
♪ As night comes,
and I'm breathin' ♪

36:16.043 --> 36:18.437
♪♪

36:18.480 --> 36:22.658
♪ As day breaks,
and I'm dreamin' ♪

36:22.702 --> 36:26.749
♪ Slow breeze
dances in the grain ♪

36:26.793 --> 36:29.665
♪ Of the answers
on a passing train ♪

36:29.709 --> 36:33.626
♪ So hold on

36:33.669 --> 36:36.455
♪ Hold on

36:36.498 --> 36:38.196
♪♪

36:38.239 --> 36:43.331
♪ Shafts of light
through the window ♪

36:43.375 --> 36:45.507
♪♪

36:45.551 --> 36:50.208
♪ A whisper of hair
on your pillow ♪

36:50.251 --> 36:51.644
[ Exhales, crying ][ Door closes ]

36:51.687 --> 36:54.995
♪ A golden sand
and a deep breath grin ♪

36:55.038 --> 36:58.477
♪ Tiny hand
and a flashbulb spin ♪

36:58.520 --> 37:00.522
her baby is fine, though.

37:00.566 --> 37:02.524
We performed a C-section.

37:02.568 --> 37:05.048
She's 32 weeks,
but totally healthy.

37:05.092 --> 37:07.703
Where's Keri now?

37:07.747 --> 37:09.705
I can take you to her.

37:09.749 --> 37:12.360
-Okay, thank you.
-[ Sniffles ]

37:12.404 --> 37:16.451
First, I need to see
her daughter, our granddaughter.

37:16.495 --> 37:20.499
I promised her.

37:20.542 --> 37:25.199
♪ Rest your tired eyes

37:25.243 --> 37:26.722
Hey, what's going on?

37:26.766 --> 37:28.985
You just got put through
the freakin' ringer.

37:29.029 --> 37:30.813
I probably deserved it, huh?

37:30.857 --> 37:34.643
Yeah, for sure,
but you're gonna make it.

37:34.687 --> 37:37.733
-What about the girl?
-She's fine.

37:37.777 --> 37:40.388
Post-op for a few days,
but there's nothing
to worry about.

37:40.432 --> 37:43.261
♪♪

37:43.304 --> 37:46.568
I owe you an apology.

37:46.612 --> 37:50.268
Everyone gets scared.
I know I do,
so I'm sorry, okay?

37:50.311 --> 37:52.748
I was in no position
to judge you.

37:52.792 --> 37:55.316
What are you scared of?

37:55.360 --> 37:57.013
It doesn't matter.

37:57.057 --> 38:00.147
I'm so high right now.

38:00.190 --> 38:02.323
I'll never remember
anything you said.

38:02.367 --> 38:06.632
All right, well, just try to
remember this, all right?

38:06.675 --> 38:08.111
You're only human.

38:08.155 --> 38:10.288
You're gonna disappoint
yourself, man,

38:10.331 --> 38:13.987
but you're also gonna surprise
the hell out of yourself,

38:14.030 --> 38:17.773
do things you never thought
you could do...

38:17.817 --> 38:19.166
as long as
you don't give up.

38:19.209 --> 38:22.735
♪ I'm burning down
a candle flame ♪

38:22.778 --> 38:25.868
♪♪

38:25.912 --> 38:30.264
♪ Been down
by the pouring rain ♪

38:30.308 --> 38:33.311
♪ Children's tunes
soft and low ♪

38:33.354 --> 38:37.445
[ Crying ]♪ From a far off radio

38:37.489 --> 38:40.883
♪ Hold on

38:40.927 --> 38:41.971
♪ Hold on

38:42.015 --> 38:44.757
She's beautiful.

38:44.800 --> 38:47.629
What do we call her?

38:47.673 --> 38:51.459
Her name is Peregrine.

38:51.503 --> 38:54.462
Keri named her after me.

38:54.506 --> 38:58.118
[ Crying ]
I had no idea.

38:58.161 --> 38:59.859
[ Crying ]

38:59.902 --> 39:05.778
♪ Rest your tired eyes

39:05.821 --> 39:11.000
♪ Tonight

39:11.044 --> 39:14.569
Hey. Hold up.

39:14.613 --> 39:18.834
Listen, I'm sorry about
your patient.

39:18.878 --> 39:20.401
You know there's nothing
you could've done.

39:20.445 --> 39:22.882
I know.

39:22.925 --> 39:24.840
I know.

39:24.884 --> 39:26.755
You did great, though.

39:26.799 --> 39:29.410
-You, too.
-Yeah.

39:29.454 --> 39:30.933
I heard
about the attending job.

39:30.977 --> 39:35.198
-Yeah.
-Congratulations.

39:35.242 --> 39:37.375
You don't seem happy.

39:37.418 --> 39:40.682
I am. It's just, uh,
the OB program

39:40.726 --> 39:43.424
that Mr. Avila
put me up for?

39:43.468 --> 39:45.426
Yeah.

39:45.470 --> 39:47.515
It's in Philadelphia.

39:47.559 --> 39:50.213
♪♪

39:50.257 --> 39:52.390
Uh, you can't do
a program here?

39:52.433 --> 39:54.653
They have the best
in the country.

39:54.696 --> 39:57.307
I wanna be the best. You of
all people should get that.

39:57.351 --> 40:00.528
You're so good
at what you do here.

40:00.572 --> 40:01.964
-No, I just --
-Mario.

40:02.008 --> 40:05.533
Do you know how good you are
at what you do?

40:05.577 --> 40:08.710
And you love it.

40:08.754 --> 40:11.234
I want that for me.
Can you understand that?

40:11.278 --> 40:13.585
Of course.

40:13.628 --> 40:18.503
So, uh, well, are we supposed to
do this long-distance or...

40:21.114 --> 40:23.943
Oh.

40:23.986 --> 40:26.162
You wanna break up.

40:26.206 --> 40:27.512
I don't want to,
Mario, but...

